# **Business Requirements Document (BRD)**

## Product: **Snap2Sheet (Working Name)**

---

## 1. **Objective**

Build a mobile application that converts images of documents (receipts, invoices, printed text) into **structured, exportable data (CSV/Excel-ready)** with minimal user effort.

Primary goal:

> Enable users to go from image → usable data in under 10 seconds.

Secondary goal:

> Deliver a production-grade mobile app to learn end-to-end product execution and App Store deployment.

---

## 2. **Problem Statement**

Users frequently deal with information locked inside images:

* receipts for expense tracking
* invoices for accounting
* printed data for reporting

Current solutions:

* extract only raw text (not usable)
* require manual re-entry into Excel
* are cluttered or over-engineered

Result:

> Time wasted + friction in converting image data into structured format.

---

## 3. **Target Users**

### Primary Users

* freelancers tracking expenses
* small business owners
* accountants (light usage)
* students handling data manually

### Secondary Users

* professionals needing quick data extraction
* anyone converting printed data into digital format

---

## 4. **Scope**

### **In Scope (v1)**

* capture image via camera
* upload image from gallery
* extract text from image (OCR)
* detect key fields (basic structure)
* display extracted data for review/edit
* export data as CSV
* share/export file via device options
* maintain local history of scans

### **Out of Scope (v1)**

* handwriting recognition
* multi-language optimization
* advanced AI document classification
* cloud sync / user accounts
* payment/subscription system
* bulk processing
* PDF/Word export

---

## 5. **Key Features**

### 5.1 Image Input

* capture via camera
* select from gallery
* preview before processing

### 5.2 Data Extraction

* OCR extraction of text
* basic identification of:

  * vendor name
  * date
  * total amount
  * tax (if available)

### 5.3 Data Review

* display:

  * raw extracted text
  * structured fields
* allow user edits before export

### 5.4 Export

* generate CSV file
* allow:

  * download/save
  * share via apps (email, WhatsApp, Drive)

### 5.5 History

* list of previous scans
* ability to reopen and re-export

---

## 6. **User Flow**

1. User opens app
2. Chooses:

   * Take Photo OR Upload Image
3. Image preview displayed
4. User taps **Extract Data**
5. App processes image
6. Extracted data shown
7. User edits if needed
8. User taps **Export CSV**
9. File generated and shared/saved

---

## 7. **Functional Requirements**

### FR1: Image Capture

* system shall allow image capture via device camera

### FR2: Image Upload

* system shall allow image selection from gallery

### FR3: OCR Processing

* system shall extract text from image input

### FR4: Data Structuring

* system shall map extracted text into basic structured fields

### FR5: Data Editing

* system shall allow users to modify extracted fields

### FR6: CSV Export

* system shall generate downloadable CSV file

### FR7: File Sharing

* system shall support native share options

### FR8: Local Storage

* system shall store extraction history locally

---

## 8. **Non-Functional Requirements**

### Performance

* extraction response time < 5 seconds (ideal)
* app should not freeze during processing

### Reliability

* graceful failure if OCR fails
* retry mechanism

### Usability

* minimal steps (≤ 5 actions to export)
* clean, distraction-free UI

### Compatibility

* Android (priority)
* iOS (secondary)

### Security & Privacy

* inform users if images are processed on server
* avoid storing images permanently
* comply with basic privacy requirements

---

## 9. **Success Metrics**

### Product Metrics

* successful extraction rate
* average time to export
* repeat usage (D1 / D7 retention)

### Technical Metrics

* crash-free sessions > 95%
* OCR success rate
* export success rate

---

## 10. **Risks & Constraints**

### Risks

* OCR inaccuracies
* poor image quality
* user expectation of 100% accuracy
* competition from existing apps

### Constraints

* limited initial scope
* no heavy backend optimization in v1
* reliance on third-party OCR

---

## 11. **Future Enhancements**

